summary:
Into the Spider-Verse (2018)
Miles Morales - Earth 1610 as in the comicbook he was born into, Ultimates earth, subsequently...
body:
Into the Spider-Verse (2018)

  1. Miles Morales - Earth 1610 as in the comicbook he was born into, Ultimates earth, subsequently destroyed in the Secret Wars event of 2015, Miles became afterwards part of the 616 canon
  2. Peter B. Parker - Earth 616 as the earth where the main Marvel Universe exists being the main line of publication of Marvel Comics.
  3. Gwen Stacy - Earth 65, also the earth where she started her career as Spider Woman in the comics, woman lead too (a female Sam Wilson is Captain America)
  4. Peter Porker - Earth 8311, also the canon numeration of its comicbook counterpart
  5. Peni Parker - Earth 14512, introduced during the Spider Verse event where also Gwen was introduced, created by Gerard Way
  6. Peter Parker - Earth 90214, a Noir genre earth where Marvel superheroes exist but in the time-frame of the 1920s onward, introduced in 2009, it has also give the spotlight to the Punisher and Daredevil.

You get the gist, and the colorful worlds they all belong to which for the most part are Earth 616, but with twists and tweaks and this is why it is bothersome that something as whitewashed, racist, homophobic, bland and colorless as the MCU, which canonically has the designated moniker Earth 19999, is trying to call itself the main Earth, the 616 one, when it has taken steps to be the ugliest blandest one and has repeatedly tried to mock and detach itself from its comicbook source.

And it’s also telling that they’re talking about this shit just a few months after Sony did it first and with much more love to where Miles Morales came from.

Fuck the MCU.
